<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Slovakia-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Deadly blaze tears through Slovakia high-rise block" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> At least seven people died and dozens were injured in a gas explosion that rocked a 12-storey building in eastern Slovakia, police said on Saturday. Local police chief Jan Golias said one person was still missing after the fire in the town of Presov, 400 kilometres (250 miles) from the capital Bratislava. About 100 firefighters battled the blaze, which hit the top four or five floors of the building and led to warnings from the fire service that the structure could collapse, local media reported. Continue reading Deadly blaze tears through Slovakia high-rise block at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard